======================================================================

--- Part 1: All n=6 tournaments with alpha_1=10 ---
Total tournaments: 32768
Tournaments with alpha_1=10: 720

alpha_2 distribution when alpha_1=10:
  alpha_2=2: 720 tournaments (H=29)

--- Part 2: Cycle structure of alpha_1=10 tournaments ---

  Type (6 3-sets, 4 5-sets, 6 dir-3, 4 dir-5): 720 tournaments
    Example: bits=153
    3-cycles: {0, 2, 4}(1d) {0, 2, 5}(1d) {0, 3, 4}(1d) {0, 3, 5}(1d) {1, 2, 4}(1d) {1, 3, 4}(1d) 
    5-cycles: {0, 1, 2, 3, 4}(1d) {0, 1, 2, 4, 5}(1d) {0, 1, 3, 4, 5}(1d) {0, 2, 3, 4, 5}(1d) 
    alpha_2 = 2
    Disjoint pairs (2):
      {0, 2, 5} x {1, 3, 4} -> 1 directed pairs
      {0, 3, 5} x {1, 2, 4} -> 1 directed pairs

======================================================================
THE COMPLEMENTARY 3-CYCLE MECHANISM
======================================================================

At n=6: two disjoint 3-vertex sets partition all 6 vertices.
There are C(6,3)/2 = 10 complementary pairs of 3-vertex sets.

Complementary 3-cycle pairs in alpha_1=10 tournaments:
  0 complementary cycle pairs: 720 tournaments, alpha_2 range [2, 2]

