======================================================================
DEFINITIVE MECHANISM: WHY alpha_1=10 FORCES alpha_2>=2
======================================================================

  Score (np.int8(1), np.int8(2), np.int8(2), np.int8(3), np.int8(3), np.int8(4)) (c3=6): 720 tournaments with alpha_1=10
    c3=6 vertex sets, 4 directed 5-cycles, need 6 directed 3-cycles: 720 tournaments
    But c3 3-cycles means 6 directed 3-cycles (each vertex set gives exactly 1).
    So alpha_1 = 6 + 4 = 10

    COMPLEMENTARY PAIR ANALYSIS:
    bits=153: 6 3-cycle sets, 0 complementary pairs -> alpha_2=2
    bits=211: 6 3-cycle sets, 0 complementary pairs -> alpha_2=2
    bits=300: 6 3-cycle sets, 0 complementary pairs -> alpha_2=2
